Original tweet:
5. Recency Bias

The tendency to overweigh the most recent information and events.

• Causes traders to lose sight of the bigger picture

• #BTC up 7,000% in the past 5 years.

  Then it down 30.03% in the last 3 months.

  You think #BTC loses its worth.

=> Zoom out
Clean tweet: 5 recency bias the tendency to overweigh the most recent information and events causes traders to lose sight of the bigger picture btc up 7000 in the past 5 years then it down 3003 in the last 3 months you think btc loses its worth gt zoom out

Original tweet:
2. Anchoring bias

The tendency to over-rely on the first information you have.

• Caused by human’s need to make estimates

• You bought #BTC at $1,000.

  #BTC surge to $10,000 is too expensive in your head.

=> Evaluate purchases based on a token’s potential, not its past
Clean tweet: 2 anchoring bias the tendency to overrely on the first information you have caused by humans need to make estimates you bought btc at 1000 btc surge to 10000 is too expensive in your head gt evaluate purchases based on a tokens potential not its past

Original tweet:
1. Unit bias

The preference to buy a whole unit of a token rather than a fraction of it.

• Leads to over-rating a token’s price over its value

• Drives the recent explosion of meme coins

• 1 #DOGE > 0.01 #BTC

=> Evaluating a token based on its merits, not prices
Clean tweet: 1 unit bias the preference to buy a whole unit of a token rather than a fraction of it leads to overrating a tokens price over its value drives the recent explosion of meme coins 1 doge gt 001 btc gt evaluating a token based on its merits not prices
